---
name: log-fueling-rehearsal
description: After Avi logs a workout that was 60+ minutes, capture the race-day fueling rehearsal data — carbs/hr, sodium/hr, fluid/hr, products used, gut response 1-10, energy response 1-10. Critical for race-day GI safety. Triggers when Avi mentions fueling, gels, salt caps, drink mix, or finishes describing a long session. Also auto-prompted by the evening-review routine when a long session lands without a rehearsal log.
when_to_use: Within a few hours of finishing a session ≥ 60 min. Don't use for shorter sessions — fueling there is essentially "drink water" and not worth structured logging.
---

# log-fueling-rehearsal

## Steps

### 1. Confirm the session

```
GET /api/workouts?since={today}&limit=5
```

Find the most recent workout with `time_duration` ≥ 60 min. Confirm
with Avi if multiple match: "Logging fueling for the {duration} {type}
that started at {time}, right?"

### 2. Ask the fuel questions

Direct, factual. Avi answers in 30 seconds. Skip questions he's already
volunteered.

- "Total carbs during the session?" (g — accept "two gels and a Maurten 320" → ~120g)
- "Sodium?" (mg — accept "salt cap × 2" → ~600mg)
- "Fluids?" (ml or oz)
- "Caffeine total?" (mg, optional — skip if not used)
- "Products used?" (free text — Maurten, Skratch, gel, real food, water)
- "Gut response 1–10?" (1 = GI distress, 10 = no issues)
- "Energy response 1–10?" (1 = bonked, 10 = strong throughout)

### 3. Compute per-hour rates

```
duration_hr = time_duration / 60
g_carb_per_hr = total_carbs / duration_hr
g_sodium_per_hr = total_sodium_mg / duration_hr / 1000
ml_fluid_per_hr = total_fluid_ml / duration_hr
```

### 4. Save the rehearsal

```
POST /api/races/fueling
{
  "rehearsal_date": "{today}",
  "workout_id": "{matched workout id}",
  "target_race_id": "{upcoming race id, if any}",
  "duration_min": N,
  "g_carb_per_hr": N,
  "g_sodium_per_hr": N,
  "ml_fluid_per_hr": N,
  "g_caffeine_total": N,
  "products": "Maurten 320 ×1, gel ×2, salt cap ×1",
  "gut_response": N,
  "energy_response": N,
  "notes": "Brief observation if Avi shared one"
}
```

### 5. Coaching feedback (one paragraph)

| Signal | Coach response |
|--------|----------------|
| `gut_response < 6` | Name what to try differently. Common: drop carb rate by 10g/hr; switch to dual-source (glucose + fructose); reduce caffeine; train the gut more gradually. |
| `energy_response < 6` | Check rate vs duration. Sessions ≥ 90 min generally need 60–90 g_carb/hr. If under-fueled, name it. |
| Both ≥ 8 | Mark as candidate race-day plan. Update `races.fueling_plan` if a target race is linked. |

### 6. Pattern check across rehearsals

```
GET /api/races/fueling/list?limit=10
```

Surface 1 sentence:
- *"Your gut handles 60 g/hr cleanly; haven't tested 75 g/hr yet."*
- *"Last 3 rehearsals all logged sodium under 500 mg/hr — race day will
  be hotter; consider 700+."*
- *"This is your highest carb-rate rehearsal that didn't crash the gut.
  Hold this protocol for race day."*

### 7. Save coaching session if it generated a decision

If you flagged a protocol change or named the rehearsal as the candidate
race-day plan, also save:

```
POST /api/training/coaching
{
  "session_date": "{today}",
  "title": "Fueling rehearsal: {duration}min — {gut}/{energy}",
  "summary": "{rate} g/hr carb at {duration}min. Gut {gut}/10. Energy {energy}/10.",
  "key_decisions": ["{rate} g/hr {confirmed for race / needs adjustment}"],
  "next_steps": "Test {next iteration} on next long session.",
  "ai_source": "claude",
  "tags": ["skill", "fueling"]
}
```

## ADHD-aware notes

- Keep questions tight. 30 seconds total.
- Don't drag him through a fueling lecture if both responses are 8+ —
  just confirm "this is the protocol, lock it in."
